reactions.notes: Overall it was a good day. Hoagie was able to recover quickly when he got upset.

reactions.description: nail trim at the vet. vet was unable to trim nails hoagie was too  upset.
reactions.notes: Hoagie received diazepam and trazadone to help him at the vet. He will need full sedation for future procedures. At 9pm he started panting and pacing, soon after he had a focal seizure. He was up with post-ictal blindness until mid-night.

reactions.description: screamed in the car on the way to a walk. redirected on Birdie. Amped up throughout the walk
reactions.notes: really excitable today - obsessive destruction endless energy

reactions.description: saw a dog in the distance. whining and leash pulling
reactions.notes: Threw-up after breakfast. I think he ate too fast. Back to the slow feeder.

reactions.description: Played in the creek. Very happy!
UPS delivery. redirected on birdie. took a long time to calm down.
4-wheelers running down our road in the evening. So much barking; redirected agression on Birdie. Pantig and pacing during the evening.
reactions.notes: He was generally amped up today. White noise helped him calm down at bedtime.

reactions.description: We were in the car too long on the way to hiking. Very vocal.
